{"key":"processedPost-9449204","value":{"id":9449204,"first":9449123,"last":9449204,"when":1229533349,"utime":"12/17/08 07:02 PM","content":"Rather than mixing up each jar, use 1 cup brf, 1 cup water, and 2 cups verm to make five or so 1/2 pint jars.&nbsp; Fill each to about 1/2\" to 3/4\" from the top and then finish with your fine dry verm until it sticks a tad above the jar rim, to account for settling.&nbsp; Put the lid on rubber side up, and sterilize.&nbsp; Don't forget to keep the jars totally out of the boiling water and cover with foil during sterilization.<br />RR","title":"Re: getting good mixture","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}